properties.areaDesc: Los Angeles County Coast including Downtown Los Angeles
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 9 at 2:17PM PST until February 11 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Areas of northeast winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts up to 45
mph expected.

* WHERE...Below passes and canyons from Malibu to the Hollywood
Hills.

* WHEN...Until noon PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and
make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Roadway affected by strong cross winds
include the Pacific Coast Highway and the 10, 110, 101 and 405
freeways.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON PST TUESDAY
